author: psharples
msg: Updated so each build is contained within it's own '/source', '/binary/standalone' and 'binary/war' folders.  Reason is because once you run the gpg -armor --detach-sig, MD5 and SHA algorithms on each archive, we end up with lots of files, so it is easier to navigate each build this way. Also it will now reflect how the structure should look like on www.apache.org/dist/incubator/wookie.

author: danielsh
msg: Only enable the workaround when we are compiled against SQLite 3.7.7.x
and earlier.  This should be safe since the version of SQLite at run-time
cannot be older than the version at compile-time.

author: hthomann
msg: OPENJPA-2006: If flushing, also pre-flush non-provisional entities to allow sequence ID population - applied Jeremy's 1.2.x patch.
